        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 7 at 7:40AM MDT until August 7 at 8:45AM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>SVRGGW

The National Weather Service in Glasgow has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Central Wibaux County in northeastern Montana...
East central Prairie County in northeastern Montana...
Dawson County in northeastern Montana...
Southeastern Richland County in northeastern Montana...

* Until 845 AM MDT.

* At 740 AM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 7 miles northwest of Bloomfield to 13 miles south of
Lindsay, moving southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Glendive, Bloomfield, Savage, West Glendive, Intake, Lindsay, Hoyt,
Hodges, Forest Park, Stipek, Marsh, Midway, and Burns.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
